DataElement.preferredName: Masseter Muscle Enlargement Sleep Bruxism Present Yes No Indicator
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A yes/no indicator related to presence of larger than normal muscles arising in the zygomatic arch that close the jaw because of an involuntary clenching or grinding the teeth during sleep.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to presence of larger than normal muscles arising in the zygomatic arch that close the jaw because of an involuntary clenching or grinding the teeth during sleep.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Muscles arising in the zygomatic arch that close the jaw. (MeSH)

Concepts.definition: A muscle of mastication originating from the zygomatic arch.

Property.preferredDefinition: The act of increasing (something) in size or volume or quantity or scope. :A natural and periodic state of rest during which  consciousness of the world is suspended.:An involuntary or unconscious clenching or grinding the teeth, typically during sleep.:Being or existing in a specified place or at the specified time.

Concepts.definition: The act of increasing (something) in size or volume or quantity or scope.
A natural and periodic state of rest during which consciousness of the world is suspended.
Excessive clenching of the jaw and grinding of the teeth.
Being or existing in a specified place or at the specified time.
